The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 LOOSE CHANGE

 ING Vysya Life Insurance has declared annual bonus rates for all its participating policyholders. It has announced simple reversionary bonus of 7.5 per cent and 6.5 per cent on policies like Powering Life and Fulfiling Life, respectively. A cash bonus of 5 per cent has been declared on both Reassuring Life and Maximising Life. Compound reversionary bonus of 4 per cent has been declared on Rewarding Life and 2 per cent for Creating Life, Reassuring Life and Safal Jeevan. The gross return on the accumulated funds in individual pension account of Best Years is 6.3 per cent.

 UTI Mutual Fund has declared a 7 per cent maiden dividend under its dividend yield fund. The record date is October 27. LIC Mutual Fund has also declared dividend under four of its schemes, including Dhan Tax Saver?96 at 100 per cent with record date on October 21, 20 per cent on ULIS and Equity Fund on November 4 and 7, respectively, while 40 per cent on Index Fund-Nifty Plan on November 8.

 Tata Mutual Fund has unveiled Tata Contra Fund, which will invest at least 70 per cent of its assets using the contrarian investment approach. The minimum investment is Rs 5,000. During the new fund offer period (till October 25), there is no entry load.




